Name: Central Park
Description: Large public park in the heart of Manhattan with lakes, meadows, and recreational facilities

Name: Times Square
Description: Major commercial intersection and tourist destination known for bright lights and Broadway theaters

Name: Empire State Building
Description: Iconic 102-story Art Deco skyscraper and popular observation deck

Name: Brooklyn Bridge
Description: Historic suspension bridge connecting Manhattan and Brooklyn

Name: Statue of Liberty
Description: Symbol of freedom and democracy, gift from France in 1886

Name: One World Trade Center
Description: Tallest building in NYC and primary building of rebuilt World Trade Center complex

Name: High Line
Description: Elevated linear park built on a former railway line on Manhattan's West Side

Name: Madison Square Garden
Description: Multi-purpose indoor arena and home to the Knicks and Rangers

Name: Museum of Modern Art
Description: One of the most influential museums of modern art in the world

Name: Grand Central Terminal
Description: Historic train terminal and architectural landmark
